Preheat oven to 400 degrees. (If you have a #grill pan{}, you can skip this!) Soak the @wooden skewers{4} in water. Place the @shrimp{10%ounce} in a #medium bowl{} with 2/3 the @coconut milk{1%can} and @sriracha{2%teaspoon}. Set aside to marinate.

> You may need to stir the coconut milk to account for any natural separation.

Peel the @carrots{1}. Using a #peeler{}, shave the @cucumber{1} and carrot into ribbons lengthwise, rotating as necessary. Thinly slice the @shallot{1}. Chop the @mint{1%bunch}. Grate or mince the @garlic{2%clove}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @peanut butter{2%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{1%teaspoon}, 3 tablespoons coconut milk, @sriracha{1%teaspoon}, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and garlic to taste. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, as desired.

Thread the shrimp onto the skewers. Place skewers on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and bake in the oven for ~{5-6%minutes}, until opaque.

> If you have a grill pan, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} on a grill pan over high heat. Cook the skewers for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until opaque and slightly charred. They will be delicious either way!

Toss the cucumber, carrot, and shallot (to taste) in a medium bowl with the chopped mint, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, and season with salt and pepper.

Serve the shrimp skewers and drizzle with the peanut sauce. Serve the cucumber salad to the side. Enjoy!